nodes.text: Enhanced Jabba's Palace was a line of cards created for the Star Wars Customizable Card Game. The product was created and produced by Decipher before losing the license to Wizards of the Coast. The line was made in an effort to get rid of excess Jabba's Palace packs.
EJP (as it is commonly called) was notable for containing a card of Mara Jade, the first live-action depiction of that character. Model Shannon Baksa posed for the image.
